title.narrative: IN Dam Rehabilitation and Improvement Project

description.narrative: To improve the safety and operational performance of selected existing dams in the territory of the participating states.The PDO will be achieved through rehabilitation and improvement of dams and improvement in central and state-level institutionalcapacity to sustainably manage dam safety administration and operation and maintenance.

condition.narrative: Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, B, 10 (LA and FA) | Description :Employ a management and engineering consulting firm toprovide assistance with project management. | Due Date :31-Dec-2012
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, B, 4 (LA and FA) | Description :Maintain at all times the Dam Safety Organization withinthe Central Water Commission. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, B, 5 and 6 (LA and FA) | Description :Maintain a Central Project Management Unit (CPMU)with adequate staff, functions, responsibilities, and resources to coordinate andmanage the project. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section I, B, 9 (LA and FA) | Description :Project funds shall not be used to increase the designedstorage capacity of reservoirs. | Frequency :Yearly
Finance Agreement :Schedule 2, Section II, B, 3 (LA and FA) | Description :CPMU to put into operation a system of quarterly reviewsof internal controls. | Due Date :18-Apr-2013
Finance Agreement :Schedule, section I, A, 4 (PA) | Description :Maintain at all times the Dam Safety Organization within the StateWater Resources Departments. | Frequency :Yearly

Finance Agreement :Schedule, section I, A, 5 and 6 (PA) | Description :Maintain in each participating state a State ProjectManagement Unit (SPMU) with adequate staff, functions, responsibilities, and resources to coordinate and manage the project withina state. | Frequency :Yearly
